Been not good PUG wise in recent days, whats the stranger things which
has happened in instances which you didn't put up with, or stuck with
and watched the wipes happen?

One run of ZF, a rogue:

Pick pocketed all mobs before the sap. Tank told him to stop. He got
mouthy. Tank left.

Unluckily rogue continued. He seemed to think his role was to solo/
tank a mob, and started shouting HEALME lots, and running out of Line
of Sight, losing the heal and dying. On being told he was a shit
rogue, he told me I should learn to play a rogue (being a 45 priest).
When told I have a 70 rogue, he seemed to think I didn't. At that
point I left...

Tank comes in Mechanar, and starts pulling mobs. Then pulling mobs.
Ok, so due to my mistake, growl  was on on the hunter, so I had to rez
it twice before noticing. But I was out of mana, as was the Warlock
beside me, but this guy kept on pulling before we could mana up....
Still pulling mobs.On asking him to stop, he said that we had
obviously not done raids. Well, yes. But on raids, there is redundancy
of on DMG providers on trash... So walked.

Rogues are not always the worse, I seem to have trouble with paladins
and the concept of a single tank too.... Yet demanding heals when they
steal the aggro from the tank...

Any other tales... I have heard friends leave pugs when the immortal
phrase is said:

&quot;Man, I am so drunk right now&quot;

Smid
