My main is a rogue. IMHO, the rogues main job is DPS beside the tank.
Crowd control is a secondary function for the rogue. Usually I have
this worked out with the healers before combat starts:
1 - main healer concentrate on the tank
2 - If there is a secondary healer, secondary can throw a heal on me
IF they have mana to spare. Again the tank comes first.
3 - Any healer that gets aggro, call for help and I'll take care of
it. Healers should feel free to heal me when I'm saving their silly
butts....

usually in instances we are using some kind of voice comms, (Skype,
Ventrilo, etc) so communication is quick.

Rogue can always pop smoke and disengage if needed (subject to
cooldown, of course). I always carry plenty of food and bandages to
keep my health up between fights. The rogue is probably the most
expendable member of the group. If the tank dies, group is likely to
wipe. If the healers die, group is likely to wipe. If the rogue
dies....eh......
If a rogue seems to be spending time doing pickpockets, ask
why...could be he's low on flash and blinding powder and scavenging
for more.....
