Well, I don't think  it's really all *that* likely that the healer is
going to be targeting whatever mob is attacking them.  Not at first.
Whether or not they're being beaten on doesn't change the fact that
they still need to be keeping the tank alive.  Who they're targeting
is going to depend a bit on how they've got things set up.  When I'm
healing I'm usually targeting the main enemy so I can see it's casting
bar and can get an idea of what's coming up that I need to heal
through.  Then I use the clique add-on so I can cast whatever heal I
want on whoever just by clicking a certain way on their portraits.
And if a mob comes towards me, I might use fade, or if I'm far enough
away from the front, psychic scream, neither of which requires me to
target the mob heading my way.  If the healer isn't using any
add-on's, they're probably going to have the tank as their target, so
there won't really be any way to find out what mob is attacking them
even if you could have two focuses.

